    "country_code": null,
    "payload": {
      "item_type": "disturbance",
      "source": "jtwc_abpw",
      "source_key": "jtwc_abpw|south_pacific_area|invest_31p",
      "content_hash": "03e9da22086faeed",
      "platform_summary": "34.9S 176.9E | winds 33-38 kt | 989 mb | LOW",
      "platform_location": "34.9S 176.9E",
      "wind": "33-38 kt",
      "risk_48h": null,
      "risk_7d": null,
      "next_update": null,
      "raw_text": "(1) THE AREA OF CONVECTION (INVEST 31P) PREVIOUSLY LOCATED NEAR \n28.2S 178.8E IS NOW LOCATED NEAR 34.9S 176.9E, APPROXIMATELY 141 NM \nNORTH-NORTHEAST OF AUCKLAND, NEW ZEALAND. THE SYSTEM IS CURRENTLY \nCLASSIFIED AS A SUBTROPICAL CYCLONE, GENERALLY CHARACTERIZED AS HAVING \nBOTH TROPICAL AND MIDLATITUDE CYCLONE FEATURES. ANIMATED ENHANCED \nINFRARED SATELLITE IMAGERY (MSI) DEPICTS A VERY WELL-DEFINED LOW-LEVEL \nCIRCULATION CENTER (LLCC) EMBEDDED WITHIN A TIGHT SWIRL OF MID-LEVEL \nCLOUD BANDS, ABSENT OF ANY DEEP CONVECTION. ENVIRONMENTAL ANALYSIS \nREVEALS UNFAVORABLE CONDITIONS FOR DEVELOPMENT CHARACTERIZED BY HIGH \nVERTICAL WIND SHEAR (20-30 KNOTS), MODERATE UPPER LEVEL POLEWARD \nOUTFLOW, AND COLD SEA SURFACE TEMPERATURES (23-24 C). GLOBAL MODELS \nAGREE ON A SOUTHWESTWARD TRACK OVER THE NEXT 24-48 HOURS. FOR HAZARDS \nAND WARNINGS, REFERENCE THE FLEET WEATHER CENTER SAN DIEGO HIGH WINDS \nAND SEAS PRODUCT OR REFER TO LOCAL WMO DESIGNATED FORECAST AUTHORITY. \nMAXIMUM SUSTAINED SURFACE WINDS ARE ESTIMATED AT 33 TO 38 KNOTS. MINIMUM \nSEA LEVEL PRESSURE IS ESTIMATED TO BE NEAR 989 MB. THE POTENTIAL FOR THE \nDEVELOPMENT OF A SIGNIFICANT TROPICAL CYCLONE WITHIN THE NEXT 24 HOURS \nREMAINS LOW.",
      "metadata": {
        "basin_section": "SOUTH PACIFIC AREA (WEST COAST OF SOUTH AMERICA TO 135 EAST)",
        "invest_id": "31P",
        "system_class": "SUBTROPICAL CYCLONE",
        "lat": -34.9,
        "lon": 176.9,
        "wind_kt_min": 33,
        "wind_kt_max": 38,
        "wind_kt": 38,
        "pressure_mb": 989,
        "development_phrase": "REMAINS",
        "development_level": "LOW",
        "bulletin_issue_at": "2026-04-12T00:00:00+00:00"
      }
    },
